article.description: — David Dixon's 17 points and 10 rebounds helped Duquesne defeat Saint Joseph's 66-56 on Saturday.
article.headline: Dixon scores 17, grabs 10 rebounds to help Duquesne beat Saint Joseph's 66-56
article.linkText: Dixon scores 17, grabs 10 rebounds to help Duquesne beat Saint Joseph's 66-56
article.story: PITTSBURGH -- — David Dixon's 17 points and 10 rebounds helped Duquesne defeat Saint Joseph's 66-56 on Saturday. Jimmy Clark III scored 15 points while shooting 6 for 11, including 3 for 6 from beyond the arc for the Dukes (15-10, 5-7 Atlantic 10 Conference). Dae Dae Grant finished with 11 points. Cameron Brown finished with 18 points for the Hawks (16-10, 6-7). Saint Joseph's (PA) also got 11 points from Lynn Greer III. Xzayvier Brown also had eight points, six rebounds and five steals. Duquesne took the lead with 9:25 left in the first half and never looked back. Clark led his team in scoring with 10 points in the first half to help put them ahead 31-23 at the break. Duquesne used an 8-0 run in the second half to build a 17-point lead at 56-39 with 5:48 left. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
